[4] USA (Washington state)
Date: Wed 22 Apr 2015
Source: KHQ [edited]
http://www.khq.com/story/28863615/health-district-confirms-case-of-measles-in-spokane


Health District confirms case of measles in Spokane
---------------------------------------------------
Health officials report a confirmed case of measles in Spokane [Washington state]. The last confirmed case of measles in Spokane was in 1994.

Kim Papich of the Spokane Regional Health District tells KHQ that there is a confirmed case of measles in Spokane. The patient went to Franklin Park Urgent Care on [15 Apr 2015], but didn't show symptoms and was not tested for measles. A staff member at Franklin Park Urgent Care told KHQ they closed at 5 pm Tuesday [21 Apr 2015] so they could contact all the patients that were in the office the same day as the patient who tested positive for measles. They also tested all staff and plan on being back open Wednesday morning [22 Apr 2015].

The patient then made 2 trips to Holy Family and was tested a 2nd time. The results were confirmed Tuesday [21 Apr 2015].

Officials are working to identify how the unvaccinated adult was exposed, but there is no indication of recent travel or contact with a known case. The measles is not related to the large national outbreak linked to an amusement park in California.

Before receiving the measles diagnosis, the person was at the Qdoba at 901 S Grand in Spokane from 3 pm to 11 pm on Sunday [12 Apr 2015]. and at North Park Racquet and Athletic Club at 8121 N Division.

[byline: Matt Pusatory]

