[5] Canada (Manitoba)
Date: Fri 24 Apr 2015
Source: Winnipeg Sun [edited]
http://www.winnipegsun.com/2015/04/24/second-case-of-measles-reported


A measles case has been reported in Manitoba
--------------------------------------------
A 2nd case of measles has been reported in Manitoba [province]. A Winnipeg woman in her 30s is recovering at home after contracting the virus while travelling in South Africa.

People who were at 3 locations -- Dakota Walk-In Clinic on Saturday, 12 [11] Apr 2015, at 9 am; Victoria General Hospital emergency room on Sunday, 13 [12] Apr 2015, from 6:40 to 11:40 am; and the Victoria emergency room waiting room on Monday, 14 [13] Apr 2015, from 4:19 to 4:41 pm -- could be at risk.

Public health officials have been contacting people who may have come into contact with the woman at those times. Measles symptoms appear 7 to 21 days after exposure, and may include fever, runny nose, drowsiness, irritability and red eyes, as well as small white spots on the inside of the mouth or throat. Public health officials say they will continue to monitor the situation. Where appropriate, people will be offered immunization and asked to restrict their contact with others to reduce the possible spread of measles.

